\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Could you tell me the year and the date you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes 1897, March
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And did you have brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes, quite a few
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, could you tell me the order they came in and what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, I couldn't tell you that. I couldn't remember that. You see, they're all dead now. I was the youngest, that's a
ll I know, but all the others, I couldn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You don't know how many more there were
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, I know how many there were. There were... well there were about 8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Including yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, some I never knew because they died before I was born. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  of them did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And when you were born, how many were still living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Er, 4, 4, including myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And can you tell who they were and what their names were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes, but I hope you won't publish it. In any case they're dead, bu
t still. Well, my eldest, the eldest was a sister named Edith and she was out in the, she wasn't at home then she used to be a ladies maid, and she spent most of her time in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And sometimes she went abroad with these various ladies she worked for, be
cause of course we used to think it was wonderful she went to Switzerland once or twice and she went to Australia twice and on one journey when she came from, when they came back from Australia they went right across the continent of America, from one end
 
to the other, so of course we used to be very thrilled. But she died a few years ago, and she was 84 when she died. And then another sister, the next one was a sister who, well she died about, somewhere about 12 years ago or something like that, she lived
 at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}. And it is her daughter that's in this hospital now. And then I had a brother, he died about 12 years ago or thereabouts and he was a regular soldier in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. He left home, not, I can just sort of remember him, but he went to, he joined the Reg
ular Army as a boy, well he must have been only a boy a few years after I was born. I couldn't sort of remember him and he went, he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} several years and then he finished his time in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and come home and by that time I was beginning to, I hadn'
t left school when he came home. I was getting near it you know and then not long after that was broke out, the First War and he was on the Reserve and of course he had to go right away and he got very badly gassed at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 pres and when the Germans first used 
gas and our people hadn't got any gas masks or anything and he got rather badly gassed and that affected him all his life. And then after that he got wounded as well, wounded on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Somme{\*\xmlclose}
 and he died, he died, well I should say about 12 years ago something like that. And then I had two brothers, I had a brother and a sister die during the First War in 1916, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid530238\charrsid7434366 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  died one day and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid530238\charrsid7434366 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 the next. A double funeral so that was a tragedy for my Mother. But that particular brother, he'd never been well, he had weak heart and my sister, she was in domestic service in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City
}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at the time and she had appendicitis. Well of course in those days appendicitis was a very serious complaint. I mean your chances of getting through, course today appendicitis is considered nothing wel
l not from the hospital point of view unless you've got it really badly, but as regards an appendicitis operation it's only passed as a very minor .... but in those days you see they hadn't well they hadn't got the medical science was so different that qu
ite a big proportion of people who had appendicitis operations used to die. Afterwards they might recover which she did, she recovered temporarily but she died, whereby of course now very few people die. But then, there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid530238\charrsid7434366 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  died before I was born. I didn't know them
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 So when you were born, there were just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  of you living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
, because there was this brother and sister who died during the war and of course they were all going to school then. This brother who eventually joined the regular army he had left school then and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 There weren't any other little children, little toddlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, there was, not after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Was there quite a gap then between you and the ones before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No not a very big gap, they were all fairly regular intervals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And did you get on well with the ones who were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh well of course we were like all children we had our quarrels, and we weren't perfect. I mean I think all children had their disagreements and little petty things and we were just what you call normal children. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 I mean every child, all children, however much they love one another they do quarrel.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 When you were a little child, you know, say 3 or 4 years old, they were too old to play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, oh no, they weren't all that much older than me they were sort of reasonable intervals between probably, probably be }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  years or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And did you spend much time with your father, did he take you out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well not really because in those days people had to work very long hours and my father like so many more used to start about }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 {\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning and come home to breakfast. Of course when it got to night he was generally too tired to play with his children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What time would he usually come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well he used to finish work about well I expect it was about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute
}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 {\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Summer and winter the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes and I think he was usually too tired to play with his children. He may, of course, with the first one 
when he was a younger man and the first children were born, he may have played with them more but you see I came along well he was, he wasn't a young man then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How old was he when you were born roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How old is he, when he died he was nearly 70 well 67 and I was about 24
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 He was about 43 when you were born approximately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And your mother, was she also in her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 40s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 She was about the same age. I don't think there was much difference. Well no, if there was it was very
 slight. There wasn't much difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I believe you said he was a market gardener, am I right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Market gardener, no, a gardener. He was a gardener at gentlem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 n's houses, for most of his life and he worked at various places and you know what used
 to happen sometimes they'd give up these country houses or they'd die or something like that but he was, he went in for gardening when he was a boy and he followed it you see, for most of his life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Would he work at several different places at one time or would he be attached to one house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no he'd be attached to one house. See usually there was a cottage, a cottage went with the place for the gardener. Well in most cases..

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You still have that sometimes today
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh the same thing appli
es of course only there aren't so many. See a lot of these big houses they've been turned into schools and institutions. There's one where my father worked just before I was born, he worked at a place at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Dedham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 he Grove at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Dedham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. At that time I've he
ard my mother say there was a Sir somebody lived there then. Well this Sir died, he either died or went away, so he gave the place up and that place now, then my father came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 to work after that that was when I was born, just after they came here. But that place, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4025596\charrsid7434366 Th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 e Grove at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Dedham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for some years now that's been an old people's home. You see a lot of those big houses have been made into that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And did your father also work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well, they used, when I\'85oh yes they always 
had to because you see, there's greenhouses have to be attended to and all that sort of thing and Sunday work or they used to then have Sunday work and all, well a certain amount of Sunday work because you see the greenhouses have got to be looked after a
nd all that you see. But when he worked in Colchester he used to have Saturday afternoons because that was a different type of place where he worked in Colchester, different, that was\'85
 they used to have Saturdays afternoons then but normally I mean, of course a lot of people didn't get any half day a week. I didn't have one when I first left school. I didn't have any half day. It wasn't compulsory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But you'd have some day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh, yes. Half days weren't compulsory when I was at school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But did your father have to work Sundays as well, did you say in the greenhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh well yes. He didn't while he was at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 because that was a different type of place. But they did have to, of course they were not working all day but they have to a
ttend, they have to attend to it because in the winter there have to be fires and in the summer the lights have to be regulated, you see and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 When your father had a cottage, did your mother have to do certain duties as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well she didn't \'85
a lot some did but she didn't and I expect it was just as well because she had a big family. Well I'm sure she had enough to do. But they do that sometimes, even now they do. But there again you see, today, a lot of them they don't have
 cottages, they have a little flat, or something like that, you see. Not only that, there's some of them live more or less on the premises in some cases and of course often, for one thing people don't have such big families and another thing a lot of the 
g
entry don't want the children there. You know what I mean, they wouldn't want anybody who'd got a big family, but of course not many people have the big families now. But there's more of that sort of thing now that they have a flat you see chauffeurs and 
all those sort of people often, instead of having a cottage, they have a flat. They are sort of on the place or near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you ever go with your father in his work. I mean did you help him at all as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No, no. I never did anything- in fact I used to hate gardening when I was young. I detested it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Do you ever remember your father taking you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes, oh yes we went out but we didn't go out much because nobody did in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Could you tell me of the sort of outing you might have had? Can you remember any outing you had with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, we didn't have many. The only outings we ever had, because nobody had them, not ordinary working class people. They didn't expect them. I'll tell you what I know about. The average l
ife of ordinary working people then was, although I lived in Colchester and Clacton was so near, we only went to Clacton once a year and that was a Sunday School treat and some children didn't go then although it was so near. And we, I attended a church h
ere, Sunday School where we always went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
. Lots of the churches and lots of the chapels especially they didn't even go to the seaside. They used to have a tradesman would lend them a horses and vans and they would go out a mile or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 2}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  in the country 
to somebody who lent their grounds and they would ...this was only half a day or half a day and the evening we'll say in the summer time and they would have sports in the field and tea and scrambles for sweets and things like that. I mean, you think of th
e
 outings today, they throw the sweets up in the air and they all fall down everywhere. Not wrapped because sweets weren't wrapped in those days, or very few any rate. I think it was exceptional to see a wrapped sweet. And, I mean they used to throw the sw
e
ets up and there was, you can imagine, a glorious scramble. Of course if they got a little dirt on nobody worried because the saying was, you don't hear it quite so much now, you, we, everybody's got to eat a peck of dirt before they die. Well I think mos
t children then ate their peck long before they left school. Well I'm sure they did. When you look back, nobody thought anything about it. But that was very few children, ordinary working class children, very few had more than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  or possibly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 days at the se
aside. It wasn't expected. Of course that day was looked forward to weeks and weeks and weeks beforehand. It was looked back on weeks and weeks afterwards. And we considered we were lucky because we went to the seaside and lots only had the treat in a fie
ld but of course today they would turn up their noses at that. Of course it was a great event.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you have to contribute some money towards it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No, no, we didn't. I don't know whether any of them did. Some may have done but we didn't. Well of c
ourse it was remarkably cheap in those days when you think of it. I mean in those days you could go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
, well say, some of the mothers used to go down you see on that day and I think it only used to be 1/3. for a day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
s return to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} but that 1/3
 had to be found and another thing, you see, there were no canteens at work in those days, well not in the country. And that meant that the man's dinner had got to be cooked, or else he'd got to take it cold with him, something cold. Well you see a lot of
 
the mothers wouldn't neglect their husbands and push them off because of that, so a lot of course didn't go but for some of the mothers that was as much of a treat to go down with the children as what it was for the children. Because that was the only, th
e
 only time they saw the seaside, although we were so near. Anyway we didn't contribute anything where I went they used to raise the money by subscriptions you see. People connected with the church would be asked to give, you see, and somebody would give t
h
em some.. we weren't a very big Sunday school and we used to take a lot of our food and then the Sunday school took a lot of our food down because we weren't a very ... weren't all that number of us and they used to do that for economy I suppose, rather t
han take us in a restaurant somewhere, you see, and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How many of you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well I'm only guessing but I should say there weren't more than 50 to 60. That's only guesswork, but there probably weren't more than about 60.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Was that a little by standards of those days, was that a small numbers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well some were bigger and some were smaller you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 St. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 J}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
ames, on East Hill, and we weren't a very big Sunday school because the person there, he wasn't liked ver
y much and he wasn't a very popular man really. And of course a lot of people didn't like him and they didn't send their children there. They didn't like him, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Why did people not like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well he was a very bigoted man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, bigoted in his religious views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, he was, he may not have meant anything but he was a domineering kind of man you know. He thought he was right, you see, there was nothing of the meek and mild curate that you read about or see taken off on the televi
sion and all that. There was nothing like that about him. Not by any means. He was right and he hadn't got any time for other people, not really. Of course, he had a band of loyal people who, who, was what you might say, faithful to him because, well, you
 
got used to him I suppose and they always lived in that parish and they stuck to that parish, you see, because it was the parish they lived in which was what applied to us. We went there because that was our parish you see. But a lot of people they didn't
 
like him, but they didn't send their children there, of course there were plenty of other places to send them to and the consequence was that we weren't such a big school as some you see, but of course some had much bigger than that. Because they varied, 
y
ou see. There again you got the little tiny chapels and that that had only got a few. You got all sorts, even in those days, you got all sorts of branches, sects, and that you know. Of course there's more than ever now but in those days there were a lot t
hat only had a few people you see..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I interviewed an old lady who been in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 1 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 of only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  in Wivenhoe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, yes, well, but we, course we used to .... you were speaking about outings. As well as this Sunday school outing we used to go, my family, 
we used to go to, about, well always twice a year, possibly three times a year, over to the place, the village, its only 10 miles from here, a place called Earls Colne. Well that was my father and mother's native place, you see. That was near where they w
ere born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Near Halstead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Yes on the way. Well at that time, besides my grandmother and grandfather living there we had several aunts and uncles all in that, round there you see. Well we used to go over during the August holidays and often we'd st
op the night you see and we'd go round and see all the various relations and we might go back for Easter and we might go at Easter and or during the August holidays, you see, but if we went }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 3}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  times a year it was very unusual. We hardly ever went in the winter although we were so near. Of course there were no buses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well we used to go by train. Then there were trains, otherwise we couldn't have got there. Well unless we'd've walked. And there were trains you see. Course it wasn't a very frequent service, but still\'85
 there were trains and that was what people used to have to. Well in the weekdays there were carriers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 carts but they went the wrong way from our point of view. You see they used to come into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose} in the morni
ng and go back in the afternoons. Well that wasn't any good. That wasn't any good to us. Besides there wasn't any necessity with the trains because we went by train you see. But we ... if we went three times a year it was most unusual but we always went t
wice but that was the limit of our outings and we were typical, that was typical of hundreds of other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
because I had some relatives who lived at Ilford and my uncle was, well we thought he was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 we thought that he was well off, well he was, he was a commerci
al traveler. Well he wasn't well off, but still he was better off than we were and he used to have a week's holiday a year. Only a few people had a week's holiday a year then, very few people had them. I mean leaving the real gentry out, very few people h
a
d a week's holiday whatever their position was but he did and he used to go, take his children, they all, all the family, they used to go to the seaside and usually they went to Clacton, usually, because they found a very nice place there where they used 
to stay and they liked it so well they used to go to the same place you see. It was very seldom they went anywhere else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And when they came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose} \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And then when they came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
, they used to come up and see us. Well you see we used to think how lucky they were to have a whole week at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
. We used to think they must be ever so well off. To think that they could have a .... I'm not saying that we were in poverty, not like that but I mean we got along, my father was never out of work but what I mean is it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 s typical of the times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You say you weren't in poverty, did you think your mother had a struggle in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh undoubtedly she did. Like most people did. You see, because they were big families with small incomes. Oh she 
had a struggle, but nearly everybody had a ... but well, they had what you might call a tight fit but of course}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 the whole idea was then with most people as long as you paid your way and didn't owe anybody anything and bought your family up respectably that was enough. Because of course in those days not many people bought things on the H.P. Not many}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 My mother never had a thing. It was looked on as a most foolish thing to do, because you see people had their work cut out to pay as they went along. Well of 
course people who did have things like that were considered ever so foolish because they were simply pouring out. Of course the attitude today is quite different. But that's how it was. Besides there wasn't much, there wasn't much H.P.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What about clubs, like clothing clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well of course we used to pay those, most people did, we used to pay in a \'85
 at the Sunday school we used to pay in a book club about 2d. a week and then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 2d. for the whole family you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no each person, each c
hild, each child. We used to have a clothing club, no it wasn't clothing, it was coal. We paid in a coal club so we used to take the money to the Sunday school and it was all on a card and then before Christmas you had this coal, you see, and I think the 
a
verage was about 2d. a week, more if you wanted to. Of course the more you paid the more coal you had and then you paid in for boots. You didn't have any clothing club. You paid in for boots you see and then when you had a certain amount in you could take
 them out and go to a certain shop and, you couldn't go anywhere, you'd go to a certain shop. Course I remember where it used to be, it used to be dead opposite the Town Hall. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 It's 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Burton{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} the tailors now but that used to be a boot shop. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And we used to go to
 that particular shop and have these boots, you see. That was a typical thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What about Christmas clubs for Christmas ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh well people did have them but my mother didn't have any. We didn't pay in any but they existed all right. Because of c
ourse it could only be for those, well a lot of people wouldn't have had much of a Christmas. Of course they're far more plentiful now than they used to be. They I think that in London and in big cities nearly everybody pays in them but they weren't so, w
eren't so common in the country districts, but I know we did pay in those, at Sunday school these clubs and I expect they had them in lots of others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What were your father's wages when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 Well I don't know exactly but they probably wouldn't have been much more than a \{ILLEGIBLE\} week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 because that was as much as .. they probably weren't much more than \{ILLEGIBLE\} 1 a week but I know that he did used to sometimes go out in the evenings and do things for people. People who'd got grape
vines and they didn't understand them or pruning roses and all that sort of thing. He used to do odd jobs sometimes for people and earn a little extra but not to any great extent. His wages were probably not more than about \{ILLEGIBLE\} 1 a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Do you know if he handed over all the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, he certainly didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 It's interesting because customs vary in different parts of the country on this often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes but the general idea and even now is that if a man ha
nds everything over to his wife and she gives him some back is that he's not much of a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
I think it's in the North West of England that it's the opposite. This varies in different parts. And so he would give your mother an allowance, would he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes he would keep some back but of course there are some men who probably some men who didn't but the general idea was that a man who did that, his wife was boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And it's the same today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well I should imagine so. I don't know really, but I
 think it is. I think the general idea is.. of course there are some women who don't know how much their husbands earn. Of course you get all this from what you read in the papers sometimes, police court cases and all that sort of thing but in fact I know
, I know one case definitely where the man has retired now but I know one case where a man just used to put his pay packet down on the table and his wife used to give him some back. I do know one case of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But you think it was exceptional?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well of course he did have something back, he used to have to buy his own drinks and his.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 This is your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Not my father, no this is a case that I know of, the man has retired now but I know that he did do that when he was working. He used to
 put his pay packet down unopened. But then of course he'd always got money in his pocket to buy himself smokes and drinks and anything else, so I mean he had something back, but I mean the general idea was that a man who gives his wife everything and she
 gives him something back he's now a man. You know that's the general idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did your mother earn anything herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes, she was only too pleased to. There weren't many opportunities in those days. My mother for a long while used to work for a 
local doctor and of course the pay was shocking. Well compared, well all women's pay was shocking then whatever they did. Judging by standards later on, but
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What work did she do for the doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well general cleaning and she did it for this parti
cular doctor, who's been dead for many years now but she worked for him for years and years. Of course the hours were long and the pay was small, but there again the money was a supplement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did she work every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Not every day oh no she didn't go every day but she used to go probably about 3 days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 A full day's work?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes and it was a full day too. It was a full day. Sometimes she couldn't, sometimes she didn't get home till 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night. Shocking. The hours of course we
re well they wouldn't tolerate it today but still that's how it was you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did she do that when you were small, when the children were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, she did that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 
Well I can remember her starting for this doctor and I was very, very young. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But
 of course we were off hand we were all going to school. And we didn't get neglected through it. But she used to go about three days a week and then there were one or two other places nearby when they were doing spring cleaning or anything extra they woul
d
 want somebody perhaps for a few days or when they had a change of servants or a servant might be ill or something like that you see, and she had, there was one or two places that they'd call on her you see if they wanted somebody temporary while they wer
e
 without a maid or, as I say, if they'd got something special, decorating in the house or a lot of extra work, but, of course, that wasn't much. There wasn't a regular thing, it couldn't be relied on. But what a lot of women used to do in Colchester, I do
n
't think you do today, I never see any sign of it, a lot of the women in Colchester in those days... you see there were all these clothing factories in Colchester, still are, only they've got different names but on see the clothing industry in Colchester 
w
as a big source of employment. Well lots of the women after they'd married used to do the same work at home. To earn, of course, there again the money was shocking. But it was all sweated labour, course they didn't look on it as that because well they'd a
l
ways been used to it you see. And of lots and lots of people used to do that. Course they married and they could do that at home and look after their children as well you see. The great snag was that they had to go a fetch this work from the factories and
 take it back. It wasn't collected and delivered for them, so they used to have to push these bundles on prams or carry them or if there were big children, the big children would have to take them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You used to see them pushing them along?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes
 I did it myself for a women because I went errands, I used, course nearly every boy and girl used to if they could. They did something in the school hours to earn a few coppers. Oh nearly everybody did. You see there were no restrictions then as to the a
g
e a child could start. I mean now a boy mustn't deliver papers or a girl, they mustn't deliver papers until they're 12 I think. But of course in those days there was nothing like that. They could ... there was no restrictions you see. Well everybody who c
ould get a job of some kind to earn a few coppers did so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What job did you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well I used to run errands for one of the neighbours and she was a women who was getting elderly and I used to take, she used to do this work and I used to not 
only do her shopping is used to take these bundles of work and carry them up to, well it was Hightons factory then opposite St. Giles church. It got bombed during the war. It used to be a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 huge
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  great tall factory and I used to take them up for her. And I di
stinctly remember she used to do what they call finishing. Er finishing trousers and they used to have to put the waistbands on and they used to have to put the buttons on and do the turn-ups, pockets and of course the money was shocking. Really, but ther
e
 again you see people were glad to earn to supplement the. I mean, and the work for women was very limited. Course it may not have been in big cities London and all that but in country towns work was very limited because, well Colchester, as I say, these 
c
lothing factories were a big source of income but apart from that and the domestic work at the people who could afford to pay somebody, I mean the professional people and doctors and people who'd got the money they could afford to have help you see and we
ll that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What did you get paid for your errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well yes, I distinctly remember it. I got 3d. a week for a long while. It went up afterwards. As I got bigger it went up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And you'd do them every afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I used to do it every time I came out of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You'd call on her house would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And that and practically all day Saturday I was on the go. I must have w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 re out. I've often thought of that. I got 3d. a week and I used to get a slice of cake and a handful of swe
ets on a Saturday and I must, the shoe leather I must have worn out doing these errands, I must have worn out far more than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9324736\charrsid7434366 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 pennyworth of shoe leather. But my father never said 'Oh you shan't do it' or 'You mustn't do it', neither did my mother. Well as I say, it was all an accepted fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did all the others in the family do something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well you see, as a matter of fact, my sister the one that died had the job before I had it. And then you see she left school, she was older than I was and when sh
e left school and got what we'd say a proper job you see I took the job over. But she used to do it before I did. But my brother he didn't do much he just couldn't, he had a weak heart. And he couldn't do much. Well when he, they kept him at school longer
 than he need have done because in those days although the leaving age was 14}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 parents could if they wanted to, they could keep them longer. There was no hard and fast rule that they'd got to come out. Course very few did keep them for the simple reason tha
t they wanted them to be out and earning, contributing to their keep. And another thing very few children wanted to stop. Very few children wanted to stop at school, because the conditions at school were very different. So my brother did, they did keep my
 
brother at school a bit longer because they realized that he would never be able to do much. When he did leave school he had several jobs but he always had to be brought home in a state of collapse, so what he used be at home and do the house work. Well m
ost of it. While my mother was out he used to do most of the housework. He could cook and he used to cook the dinners and everything and of course my father and mother had to keep him, keep him in clothing. Of course, we never\'85
 my mother would be too proud 
anyway to ask for any assistance. Of course they wouldn't have any scruples about that today. I mean there's lots of people like that now that well they just get national assistance you see but my mother wouldn't have, well she wouldn't have brought herse
l
f to do it anyway. Besides it wasn't easy to get, but anyway so I mean they had him to keep you see and he used to do the housework and do cooking and all that. He could cook a dinner as well as my mother could and, but, normally children didn't stop afte
r
 they were 14. Not many and they didn't want and the parents wanted them out earning something too. But nearly, most children used to do a job of some kind. Delivering papers, or some of the big houses had a boy to do some of the rough work because you se
e
 there were no labour saving devices in these big houses. What we think today, I mean there were all coal fires and the coal had to be got up from the cellar in the winter and knives to be cleaned, because there was no stainless steel and boots and all th
at sort of thing that a lot of the people used to have a boy between school hours to do all that. That sort of thing. Course he got a little money every week and he was happy and his parents were happy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 In the home did you have any jobs as a regular duty to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes we all had to do a bit of share in the housework you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you have any particular set job each of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well not in our family, course a lot of people did. Every child had its job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But in your family you shared
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes we used to do odd jobs. Mother used to be at work a lot you see and we used to help with the, you know, general cleaning and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Can you tell me something about the kind of meals you had as a child because this has changed somewhat? In you
r own particular family. How did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well we had normal meals you know. Breakfast before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well I can't really remember but I supposed it was bacon and bread and jam. Of course there
 used to be a lot of jam in those days. Children used to eat a lot of jam: I don't know whether they do so much now but they used to them. We used to have bread and butter and jam, bacon and eggs. Eggs weren't so plentiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you have eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 We had them but although they were cheap, people didn't use them as freely as they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How often do you think you'd have had an egg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well we might have had two in a week but we didn't have a lot more not even when they were cheap because they 
weren't used as freely as they are now and another thing, there wasn't so much of this cereal thing. The only thing really that I can remember in those days was what we call porridge now and that was Quaker Oats was the main thing. That was the chief in t
hat line that you heard about was Quaker Oats. There may have been one or two other brands but...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you have Quaker Oats in your family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh we used to have Quaker Oats and, er well, and then they used to sell what they call oatmeal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8919387\charrsid7434366 I don't know whether it's sold now or not. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well its a kind of...same sort of thing, you see, and for dinner, we, our family, one of the principal things because my father was very fond of them and he used to say that he could eat them every day of the week, he didn'
t eat them every day in the week but he was very fond of, was a meat pudding. Steak and kidney pudding. And of course meat was remarkably cheap compared with present day standards, and we in our family had an awful lot of meat puddings but I can't remembe
r getting tired of them. I don't remember getting tired of ...course Sunday we had a joint. Everybody had a joint on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What kind of joint did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well it all depended on the family. You know, like they do now, they have beef one week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 That's what you used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
And then they'd have pork another for a change you know, and all that sort of thing. Well usually, usually for Sunday night supper they'd have some of the cold meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 That's what you used to have. In your own family you'd have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, that was always a recognized thing on Sunday nights. And of course in the season at the time of the year, we'd have new potatoes and peas, we did. You could have them cold as well, with the meat, and that used to be a r
ecognized thing, you know, Sunday night. You didn't have them any other night. Course other nights, well as children I suppose we just used to have bread and jam or cheese, but not so much cheese as people eat now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What did you have .. did you ever drink milk?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well I don't remember that we had much milk, not to drink it as milk because for my part I was never fond of milk, not in, only when it's cooked or boiled and I.. not now. I wouldn't say thank you for cold milk, to have a drink of cold mil
k. I used to have milk but it's all cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You were saying that parents didn't come up to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Very few. You see if a child went home and complained that they'd been punished, you see most of the parents would say 'Oh well, it'll do you good
'. You see they believed.. one of the mottos in those days was 'Spare the rod and spoil the child' and they believed of course that that was necessary for you to be corrected, because they'd had the same thing themselves and most people believed that that
 should be so and they would just say 'Oh well you must have been doing something you shouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Is that what your own parents would have said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes I think they would. Because you see that was the idea to let a child to be pampered, what they cal
l pampered, you know spoilt, it was only laying up trouble for the parents later on. There weren't many spoilt children because people had such big families, well most people had such big families that they just couldn't spoil them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What were your own parent's views on discipline and bringing you up? Can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, well I think they took the same view. My father didn't... I never remember my father punishing us excessively but he'd only got to speak sternly to us, you see, and we knew 
what it, we knew that we'd got to obey it, you see, but as for being, what you say, corporal punishment, I don't remember. If we annoyed him, he would, he'd be, you know he'd just be ever so strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 In the way he spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 He had to, we knew we'd better.. and that was the.. course you did get some parents who were a b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 t cruel to their children, no doubt, but the general idea was that it was good to have a.. to be corrected.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And do you remember any punishments at all? Ever being punished as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well this, no I don't remember any but I do remember one thing. This particular schoolmaster, he really was.. he wasn't an honorable man, he certainly wasn't, because I had no difficulty with my lessons when I went to school. I mean the lessons
 didn't worry me, but I didn't like him: I don't think many people did like him. And this particular brother of mine who I say was kept at school longer because of what he'd got wrong with him. My brother did something at school and this headmaster punish
e
d him very severely with a cane so that he went home in a state of practically collapse. Well my mother was, she was certainly by no means an aggressive woman but it must have been pretty bad because she made up her mind that she was going, and she did, g
o
 down and tell him off about it, you see, because she said that you knew what his condition was, she said, I'm not saying that the shouldn't have been punished but she said you could have punished him in some other way. But he never went back to school an
y more after that. But he wasn't at all a nice man. I always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How old were you when he was your school teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well about, that was the first school I ever went to. I would have been about, er, I would have been about, somewhere ro
und up to about 9 then, from about the time I was 6 to 9 he was schoolmaster and then that particular school, I was telling you last time, this parson, who I said wasn't liked. You see it was a church school and this parson was, well, he was an autocratic
 
sort of a man and he decided.. there were two schools, and he decided that he was going to amalgamate these two schools, these two church schools, they were both in his parish and he was going to make the bigger one of them just for girls and infants. All
 the boys had got to be cleared out and the children from this other school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434366  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Pinstead}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, it isn't a school now, they were coming to this other one, you see. Well there was a lot of argument at the time and he was a very obstinate man, he had his way, and 
of course the Education Committee must have been at their wits end what to do to find us somewhere to go and they were, they had started to build this new school in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 Pinstead}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366  Road and as a makeshift, as a temporary makeshift, they hired a Congregational Cha
pel up in Harwich Road, its still there but it's been extended and make bigger and we went there, boys, went there for about 2 years while the other school was being built and we all used to be packed in one room. All the standards from 1 till 7, if you c
a
n imagine that. Course there wasn't a great... the numbers of us weren't great but, probably a hundred, but there was every... course the classes are different now but in those days it was Standard 1 up to standard 7 and if you did your normal year in eac
h
 standard that saw you through until you were 14. Well anyway we were all in the same room. There was a curtain went across one end and there was about 3 standards in that, just curtain, it didn't go up to the ceiling and in the other part, the bigger par
t
, there were 4 standards, a lady teacher had two and there was no division, only an aisle, a little aisle and the other side was this headmaster, this horrible man and he'd got standard 6 and 7 and ex 7. Course there weren't many what they used to call Ex
 
7, there never used to be many in that because by the time they got to that, most had left you see. And they were all doing lessons in one room. If you can imagine it. And you could hear what the other.. you see all the people this side of the curtain cou
ld hear what was going on the other side. Of course that was exceptional. You see that was only a temporary arrangement but some of the little church schools weren't much better. They had several cad classes in one room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 In that school, do you think it made the work more difficult for you personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh it must have done, it must have made the work more difficult it didn't used to worry me much because I was good at lessons. But of course it used to.. I should say in those days there were more dull children than there are today. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 I know it's only my opinion but it seems to me that most children today they look so bright and cheerful.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But to get back to yourself, did you like all the lessons or did you have especially good subject?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I use
d to.. there was nothing.. there was only one or two things I used to dislike and I disliked them very much. One was drawing and the other was painting. Art. I was never any good at that and I just used to hate them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Why do you think you disliked painting? Were you bad at it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well I think every child's got its likes and dislikes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No I wondered if it was because you had an unpleasant teacher
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No it wasn't that, I just didn't like them. Because when I went to this new school, we had a muc
h different type of teacher altogether and he was very keen on art himself and we got more of it with him and I used to hate it more than ever. But all the other things, you see, ordinary arithmetic and that, they never used to worry me but of course I ha
v
e seen children just sit and nibble their pens, just didn't know what to put. Course some children they, they, well if the child got so big, you know, it grew up so much and they weren't advanced enough to be moved into another standard, well the time wou
ld come when they would just move them up so they wouldn't just be a great big boy or girl sitting amongst the little children. That used to happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But you always went up every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I went up, well the majority did I went right through and I di
d my year in everything. I did my full year in the Ex 7 and all. Not many used to go through Ex 7 because, well, they'd had a month or two in it but then they've left you see. But it was no more than 7 really because when you got in Ex 7 often, you'd have
 the same teacher. It wasn't a special class and you merely, it was merely a repetition of what you'd had in 7. You was all there with 7, you didn't get anything different, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What age were you when you actually started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well I thin
k I must have been 3 because you could go.. I don't know whether it was compulsory or whether they only permitted it, it may have been compulsory, I don't know but a lot used to go at 3.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, it wasn't compulsory, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No, but if they could take you in, they would. I went at 3.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Do you remember when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well I can't remember the first few days but I can remember what the room was like. Oh yes, I came by that old school the other day. I looked in the windows, but of course it's all been altered. The school still exists..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You mean St. James?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Yes, it still exists, but, course I looked in the window, but course it's all altered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You were on the left hand side, were you where they have the play group now?
