They have built the modern extension in the last two or three years. Course, well, when I went to that one that was a very primitive school. And the room I went in, had a, was what they call the infants, the babes they used to call it then. Ther
e was a kind of a gallery all up on wooden steps, up one end, where you sat on, well I can't remember, forms I suppose but of course that gallery's all done away with naturally and I remember there was a bead frame where you counted beads and also I can r
e
member that the teacher used to hang letters up, a card with A, B, C, D. and hang them up and I can remember there was a fireplace and over the fireplace there was a case, a glass case, not with books in but with birds eggs and curios, but there again at 
that particular school, there was only three rooms for all the lot, so you got;
\par 
