\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 How did they divide them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well they were just divided with wooden partitions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But I mean how were the ages and standards divided?
