 on Friday nights, store them in a place down near the Eastgates crossing which doesn't exist now where they used to be stored and they used to bring the pews back, well they weren't pews, they were forms then, they used to bring them back on Friday night
s
 and on Monday mornings they used to take them out, so the people that went to chapel on Sunday they'd got maps and all sorts of paraphernalia hanging around and the pulpit used to be on wheels and they used to be pushed up in a corner. Then there was one
 
little room where occasionally the bigger boys, this master used to take some of the bigger boys, the older classes, 6 and 7 he used to teach and sometimes he'd take them into another one of his smaller rooms for a special class on its own. But that didn'
