Not especially. Of course the great things at election times then, of course children don't take any great interest, but I can remember that when there was a general 
election it was far more exciting than they are today. People used to get worked up about them, but it was the excitement in our drab lives or what we call drab now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And also there were public speeches too
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh yes and they used to.. one thing th
ey used to do that you don't see now, people on both sides didn't mind how much they disfigured their own places. They gave a whole front of their houses covered with posters and propaganda and of course when I went to school the main thing then, course w
e
 didn't understand, was Free Trade and tariff reform. And I can remember there used to be the posters with the big loaf and the little loaf and all that sort of thing you know. And then of course as children, well they still do today to a certain extent, 
t
hey run behind in their, well they weren't mini cars then, they'd boo or cheer. Well they didn't know what they were doing then but it was a form of excitement then: in fact election day was a treat for these where the schools were commandeered to vote in
. Course there used to be more schools commandeered for voting than there are now. Course children who went to a school that was closed for, because they wanted to vote in it, course they got an extra day's holiday compared with the others, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I was going to ask you about when your family actually moved to Colchester. You say it was about the time that you were born?
