initely.. Every school was the same. You had, you might get children who came from a family that wasn't quite so big and therefore those children would be better off, or some children would be the remaining ones who weren't out at work. If the older ones 
w
ere out at work the consequence was that those parents were better off and then of course you'd got some perhaps that there were lots in the family younger than them and the mother couldn't go to work because she'd got the youngsters to look after, becaus
e there were no day nurseries and of course, you got different degrees.
\par 
