\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You didn't come into contact with them you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, I never came into any personal contact but I do remember one typical thing, I remember a woman who went to work at a curate}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 \rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
 at one of the churches, a young married man with several children and this woman who used to go out to help, I suppose his wife coul
d just scrape enough to employ a woman one or two days a week to do things and this woman said there were sort of what's called struggling, not to keep up with the Jones's as we say today, but to keep up appearances, you see, he sent his children to the g
rammar school, his girls to the other one, but he undoubtedly had a struggle. Course till he got promotion and got moved to be a vicar somewhere like that, but of course that used to be the case very often. You see a lot of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 lergy had private means and 
of course they were all right. They used to employ curates at a very low wage. Well some of these curates hadn't got much at the back of them, not financially, and of course, naturally they wanted their children to have the best possible education and of 
course they, it meant that they had to scrape and scrimp you see. And that was a typical, a typical thing you see, because the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15684215\charrsid7434366 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 lergy, their incomes there was no equality, it was just a matter of luck, it was what they call a good living or a rich living or
 perhaps they.. would employ a curate who had to do a good deal of the work and the curates didn't get much money, but of course now they get a standard rate, but I mean it was a question in those days more or less, well they were in the same class as the
 working people to an extent, but at school, oh I don't think there was any snobbery but as I say I didn't have any contact with grammar school boys.
