Oh yes, some of them. There was one I know, I think it was a favourite of mine. I think her name was Florence Meynell. I can't remember the name of the title of the book but I know I was fond of it and I read it over and over again. It was
 the Sunday School prize. I don't think it was so religious as some of them were. And the weekday school they wouldn't be so, er, so much, they'd be ordinary like well, what were called classics in those days. They'd be boys school books by G.A. Henry, he
 was a favourite, and Jules Verne and the girls had 'Little Women' and 'Good Wives' and you know that..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 So they were books that the children could enjoy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh they did, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 What about Dickens, did you ever get Dickens as prizes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well
 we did, we did, but I personally didn't like them. I didn't like Dickens, and I may be unusual, though I used to do a tremendous amount of reading but I didn't like Dickens. And I mean I had 'Pickwick Papers' for instance which was supposed to be one of 
the most amusing, but even that I didn't care for. And then we had, we used to get adventure tales about Canada the Pathfinders. And then of course everybody had 'Tom Brown's Schooldays'. Course that was old-fashioned really and... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Yes, yes, course it was old fashioned, but of course everybody had that. And they used to get a certain amount of war books you know, well some of them were imaginary, you know about Red Indians and all that sort of thing, they were most typical but
 of course I say the Sunday school were generally on a religious side and that was the thing, you never had anything else except books. But I think that that died out in council schools after a time, and then we used to get medals for attendance. Oh yes I
 had them for seven years running. You didn't get a medal every year, you'd get a bar put on
