emporary school, I was ill once in the winter with a very bad cold and my mother said I shouldn't go and I stopped at home, which was a, course I was lucky enough to have very good health, and she said you know, I shouldn't go that day, and I'd nearly com
p
leted a year's perfect attendance and they sent up for me at school to say could I manage to go if I only sat by the fire so that they could mark me as present so that I'd qualify for the medal, so I did that. I just went and sat by the fire all day, but 
