 school was on the... if a child had a perhaps a very prolonged kind of illness perhaps the mother would go down and see the Headmistress or the Master and explain that or... very rarely if the child was excessively punished they might go and complain but
 
that was very rare. But as I say if they were away long the attendance officer was soon round. There was no such thing as inviting the parents round to see the work. Oh no it was a world apart. The only thing the rents knew about the school was er we've g
ot a new teacher, she's, ever so what we call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2715693\charrsid7434366 \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
stingy'. You know what I mean, stingy. She used the cane, that used to be a word. I don't know if they use it now, say 'Oh she's stingy' and that meant she used the cane more then... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 The others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Most of them used to have it quite frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 They did? To the girls as well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, in some cases. At the last school I went to it was an entirely different type of teacher that I'd ever ... he was entirely different type of man altogether. He used to call all the girls by their Christian names. I've never heard...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 In those days it was surnames usually was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 The boys Oh yes, and then they used to call them by their... they used to call the little girls by their Christian names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Instead of by their surnames you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Yes, he was an entirely.. he was what you might call a modern man. Well he came from, he came you see from a Council school. He hadn't been in Church schools, because you see these Church schools wer
e really far behind the times compared with the Council schools you see because they used to work a lot more on scripture and religion. You didn't have it all day long, but I mean they made more of a point of that than the Council schools did, and of cour
s
e in lots of cases you see, the parson domineered, dominated the school and well there wasn't any comparison you see. And because of course in a village everybody had to go to the village school whether they were church or chapel or anything else. Of cour
se in a town there was more a bit more choice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 So at your school was it all Church of England, all the pupils, were they all Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Not necessarily, no, even down at this first school I went to which was definitely a church school an
d it was domineered by the person. Well on Ascension Day and Ash Wednesday, do you know what I..? well we all had to go up to the church for a service in the morning and after that it was a day's holiday. But there were some children that had got non-conf
ormist parents and they could make an application for the child not to go and they didn't have to go to the church, course they had the holiday just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And did the parents usually bother to make the application?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh some did. Oh there were 
some who did. Yes 'cause people were... people were very intolerant. You know the seats were more intolerant with each other. If you were Church you were Church and if you were Chapel, you were Chapel, and of course Roman Catholics were looked }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4000104\charrsid7434366 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 n with susp
icion, with very great suspicion and that. It's... when you look back and you see the difference today, I mean there wasn't so much tolerance. People were more narrow-minded, you see, oh yes, it was definitely church or chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you go to Church every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh we used to. Well we only stayed away on very rare occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did you all go together, the whole family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh no, we didn't all go together. We used to go ... in our particular case we used to go to the Sunday School first and
 we carried right on from Sunday School to the church service. And then we used to go to church again in the afternoon. But parent's used to go at night, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Your parent..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 My used to go at night, being ordinary working class people. Not a 
lot of them used to go on Sunday mornings, there was too much cooking to do. You see, on Sunday it might be in lots of cases the only real hot meal the man had in the middle of the day. According to what his work was. You see, if he was working somewhere 
w
here he couldn't get a hot meal, there were plenty like that because there were no canteens at work and then the other thing, the other hot meals would have to be at night, well Sunday was his great day. You see he could have a hot, a really good hot meal
 
and of course, however he, however poor people were they always reckoned to have a good Sunday dinner. They always reckoned to have a joint on Sunday even if they didn't have much the other days. So I mean there weren't many that had got a big family that
 
went to church in the mornings, not then. Of course you might get some of the non-conformist type of people: in fact I had some relations who were non-conformists and they were very strict about Sunday. They wouldn't cook on a Sunday, they cooked on Satur
d
ay and had their joint and they never cooked on Sunday not even in winter, only perhaps the potatoes, you see. It wouldn't matter if it was perhaps cold weather, no they wouldn't cook much more than their potatoes. The rest of the stuff was cold. They wer
e strict and there were people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
But in your family was Sunday ... did your mother and father have any rules about behaviour on Sunday, were you allowed to play and do what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh we weren't, we weren't restricted any more than so
me children, but on the other hand, we weren't allowed to run wild. I mean, there was a lot of things you er, well I think the great majority grew up like that. You see on Sunday you put your best clothes on and you didn't do any work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 You were allowed to play and sing and?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Well not play so much, you read more you see. You went to Sunday school in the morning and then you went direct from Sunday school to church service and in our case we used to have to stop all through the sermon and everythin
g whereby, often the children were let out before the sermon. Well young children at any rate, because they, well they realised that children can't take ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 The sermons were long, weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh they were longer then. Well in our particular ca
se we used to have to stop the whole time. Well the Sunday morning was gone and when we used to go to Sunday afternoon church as well, when we came out then we'd probably go for a walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 With your parents, or just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh well, no, the c
hildren. Well we might possibly or we might go and see relations. They lived locally you see. I mean it used to be a great thing for people to go and have Sunday tea with relations you see. That was a common
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Would your mother and father go with you if you went to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, if we went to see relations we'd stop to tea or they'd come down to yours to tea. You see that was a general, well it is now you see. Course Sunday was the only free day I mean, often people didn't see each other only on Sun
days because they worked too many hours. Of course there wasn't so much trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4000104\charrsid7434366 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
ling done on Sundays because, well for one thing it wasn't reckoned to be, not exactly respectable, but it wasn't done. And not only that, there wasn't the means you see, and wit
h even the carrier's carts that went through the country in the week, well they didn't run on Sundays. So I mean, and very few people had got bicycles. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 When did you get a bicycle, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Oh not, I was almost, most, not till I
'd been at work a long while and could earn. Then I had to start with a second hand one which most, nearly everybody did, because you see very few people had things on H.P. and generally the boys that you saw on bikes were generally grammar school boys, b
u
t otherwise bikes were very rare for children and if they'd got one it was generally one that an elder brother or sister who'd been at work had gone and bought a better one and they'd just given the old one and I mean no children, they hadn't got enough m
o
ney to buy them. Oh there was nothing. Of course now nearly everyone's got a bike. The same with watches. You didn't ... not many boys had a watch until they were going to grow up a bit, but I mean, so on Sundays you see, well the trains ran on Sundays. O
f
 course there were no buses because they didn't exist and very few people had got bikes. Course there were some people specially those who lived in the country had got little pony traps and vehicles and that sort of thing. But in towns not many people had
 
got them in towns you see and I don't think the ordinary, what we call cabs, you know what I mean, I don't think those used to run on Sunday. What plied for hire, you know what I mean. I don't think they used to run on Sundays because you see there were n
o taxis then and of course people used to have cabs and for getting about from the station and the doctors used to, some doctors used to use them you see, and then not only that you see when women went trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4000104\charrsid7434366 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 ling, they had an enormous lot of luggage and gre
at big hats and all that sort of thing. And they used to have great big hat boxes and therefore they wanted something to put all this luggage in. You see whereas now they pack the ... suitcase, but I don't think the cabs used to run on Sundays, I'm almost
 sure they didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And then when did you change out of your Sunday clothes, just before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh not till you went to bed, oh no, and they were put away. They didn't come out until next Sunday unless there was something very, very spe
cial on during the week because of course they had to be taken care of. And they were all put away. And it had got to be something very special if they came out in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Can you remember if you ever had grace at meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well a lot of people did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 But you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
I can't remember that my family did. My father never professed to be a strictly religious man, you know what I mean but I, but we didn't but they used to have it at school. We had it at school at the church school but not the other
 school. You see the other schools didn't concentrate much on religion. You had it the first thing, a little, but they didn't concentrate on it so much as they did at the church schools. Of course the church school teachers were always church people thems
e
lves, and the masters and very often Headmaster or even the Headmistress might be the organist or Sunday school teacher and all that sort of thing you see. They were definitely church people and of course they concentrated more on religion you see. The Co
uncil school didn't make anything nearly such a point you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Did your mother have any interests which she was able... did she have time to have activities outside her home and her work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 No, no,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 She just did her work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 It took her whol
e time up and she was only typical of thousands and in any case there wasn't much on in those days. You know what I mean. There were no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4000104\charrsid7434366 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 omen's Institute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4000104\charrsid7434366 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
, there were no.... well it was looked on that a woman's place was in the home and she had enough to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 I'm sure she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 She did have enough to do because you see all our place was.. had to be black-leaded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Can you tell me something about the cottage, your first home you lived in? How many rooms it had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Well it had four rooms but tw
o of them were tremendously big ones and although they were old-fashioned, they were old fashioned cottages and they were tremendously big, well the front rooms could have been partitioned off and made into two. They could, but they weren't, but they coul
d have been, because I can...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 Were they on the ground floor, both rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7038994 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 
Oh yes, and then the bed, oh no I mean the downstairs front room and then there was a kitchen and then the front bedroom was just as big as the, and then you see there was 
another bedroom. I mean they could easily, the front rooms could easily been partitioned off and made into two and then we moved into a, we moved out of there into East Hill. That was a different type of house altogether. They were, the rooms there were o
f a more uneven size.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid81562 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11816647\charrsid7434366 And how many rooms did that have?
