Well I think that when we were very little of course we slept in the big bedroom with a curtain along when we were very little and then of course as we grew 
older the eldest ones went out to service and all that sort of thing and there weren't so many of us there and we just, well father and mother had the one room and the boys had the other. Course when people came, when you had relatives come to stay, well 
y
ou just put up a bed-chair in the front room downstairs. You see. The same thing happens today and there. I mean you know you had a different type of bed-chair then. It hadn't got the, they hadn't got these settees and all that then, the chairs that folde
