 ... one thing especially that I thought of that I didn't mention before; there used to be sometimes p
rivileges in working for people. I mean, lots of firms, if a man wanted to move ... which people often did move from one house to another, because the houses were there, and if he wanted to move an a Saturday afternoon, the fellow'd lend him a horse and c
art free. 'Course, that didn't happen every week, but I mean, that was a thing that ... well, it was often done.
