 was about - besides the two bosses there was about 4 or 5 men and 3 or 4 boys. No girls or women, not then. 'Course, girls and women, they didn't do anything nearly the variety of work they do now. Some were shop assistants, if they were sort of qualifie
d
. 'Course, in Colchester, a lot worked in clothing factories because we always had a lot of clothing factories; and some would be shop assistants, and most clerical staffs were male. Most of them were. Then, of course, you'd got a ... in a place like Colc
hester you got a fair proportion of domestic servants because you had a fair proportion of people who could afford to employ them.
